ROB Details


                                                                                                                                             Guidance Notes



    Enable MIRROR Onboard


    There should be little to no increase in workload for you. The following process is to be used to enable MIRROR on-board:


    • For best  experience  use a preferable browser like  Google Chrome  to access the form.
    • By default the noon form will be displayed. If you instead wish to access a different form, you can do so by clicking the applicable tab at the top of the form


    How to use the MIRROR on Network Computer?


    In order to avoid any data loss, it is advised that only one user access the form at a time. 

    When opening the form in Google Chrome – Users have to change the “Downloads” settings for the browser to prompt user where to save each draft file before downloading, as the default setting in the browser is to save it on computer’s “C Drive” which is generally not accessible by any other user on the network. 

    To change this, follow below steps and refer to the screenshot:

    • Go to Settings
    • Click “Downloads”
    • Toggle the button next to “Ask where to save each file before downloading”


    Sending MIRROR Reports to BOSS


    • At the appropriate time, kindly fill in the requisite report as and when required (note that you can only complete one form at a time). After filling out all the details in the form you need to press the submit button at the bottom of the form.
    • A popup will appear with the generated report details.
    • The vessel needs to copy the whole text and paste it into the email body. The vessel needs to send it to our dedicated email address  mirror.reports@bwesglobal.com  and copy all the concerned parties as required
    • Continue to use the file on your desktop/shared folder and for submitting reports throughout the course of voyages under BOSS (Blue Water Optimum Speed Services)


    Avoid Refilling All Details Using Save Draft Feature


    To avoid filling all the fields in the MIRROR form while sending reports, the form comes with a "Save Draft" option  available  in top right of the form. The vessel may use this to create a copy of the HTML form with filled values.

    The next time vessel fills a report, all the pre-filled values will populate the fields and the vessel may edit them as desired.


    MIRROR Reporting Sequence


    Please refer to the MIRROR Reporting Manual sent along with the onboarding e-mail. 


    How to fill the In Port/In Transit Noon Reports?


    The vessel needs to select the Report Type from the voyage details section as  IN PORT or IN TRANSIT (for canal transits, etc.) in the Noon report form.


    ROB Calculation for Loading Operation & Reporting in Subsequent Report?


  • Loaded quantity cannot be integrated directly in cell “Load./Disch” because it is counted as consumption.
  • Loaded quantity must be added in cell “Previous ROB” corresponding to previous report ROB + loaded quantity.
  • Current ROB in the report will be Previous ROB quantity defined above minus consumption between previous report and current report.


    Example:


    If a vessel has to report ROB details for 20th Noon Report, which is after the vessel conducted the loading operation, refer below:


    1. 19th Report ROB = 15000 m3
    2. Vessel loaded quantity = 5000 m3
    3. 20th Report “Previous ROB” Cell = (15000 + 5000) + Total Consumption (from 19th - 20th)
    4. Current ROB = Previous ROB (above) – Total Consumption (from 19th – 20th)


                       ROB Calculation for Discharging Operation & Reporting in Subsequent Report?


    • Discharged quantity cannot be integrated directly in cell “Load./Disch” because it is counted as consumption.
    • Discharged quantity must be deducted in cell “Previous ROB” corresponding to previous report ROB - discharged quantity.
    • Current ROB in the report will be Previous ROB quantity defined above minus consumption between previous report and current report.


    Example:


    If a vessel has to report ROB details for 20th Noon Report, which is after the vessel conducted the discharging operation, refer below:


    1. 19th Report ROB = 15000 m3
    2. Vessel discharged quantity = 5000 m3
    3. 20th Report “Previous ROB” Cell = (15000 - 5000) + Total Consumption (from 19th - 20th)
    4. Current ROB = Previous ROB (above) – Total Consumption (from 19th – 20th)


                       How to Report BOG Details When Vessel is Operating a Reliquefaction Plant?


                      In case a vessel is operating a reliquefaction plant, the reported NBOG and FBOG values should be equal to the total LNG consumption and the reliquefied BOG for the duration.

                      Please follow the below steps to report the BOG details in the NBOG (m3) and Forced BOG (m3) fields:


      1.     Total LNG Consumption = 108 m3
      2.     Reliquefied BOG = 94 m3
      3.     NBOG+FBOG = 202 m3


          Vessel Specific Form Alerts and their Solutions


          The MIRROR form incorporates vessel-specific validations sourced from the Ship  Particulars/Form B.  In case the user enters a value for a data field higher or lower than the given range,  the form will generate a warning.


          Following are the errors that may generate in case an invalid value is entered:


          • Deadweight (MT) should be in range 37000 : 90000
          • Draft (m) should be in range 6 : 12.5
          • RPM should be between 50-90
          • Cargo Volume (m3) cannot be greater than total LNG capacity
          • Shaft Power (kW) should be less than 12520 kW
          • Main Generator Load (kW) cannot be greater than 6400 kW

          Note: The vessel may request for a new form in case a certain validation is to be updated.


            I Have a Technical Problem. Who Do I Email? 


          If you are facing any technical issues or have a feedback, you can contact the BOSS Operations Team at boss.shell-lng@bwesglobal.com.
